      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Ka">Gokhale 1991</ref>. Some of the readings seem unsecure to me (AO), so I have not tagged them.</p>
	<!-- NB Gokhale also refers to Burgess and Indraji (CTI)
	     and Bühler (BuhlerKa) !-->
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  <placeName key="pl:Kalyāṇa">kaliaṇa</placeName>sa 
	  negamasa cita
	  <lb n="2"/>kiyasa 
	  <persName key="pers:Punarvasu">punavasuya</persName> tasa
	  poḍhi deyadhamaṃ
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  This is the meritorious gift of a cistern by 
	  <persName key="pers:Punarvasu">Punarvasu</persName>,
	  the son of a trader Cita from 
	  <placeName key="pl:Kalyāṇa">Kalyāṇa</placeName>.
	</p>
      </div>
